Title: Symphony No. 9 in D Minor, Op. 125 "Choral": IVc-j. Presto. O Freunde nicht diese Töne – Prestissimo
Artist(s): Ludwig van Beethoven, Janet Perry, Agnes Baltsa, Vinson Cole, José van Dam, Berliner Philharmoniker, Herbert von Karajan, Wiener Singverein, Helmuth Froschauer
Comment: We all know Ode to Joy, right? Have you ever actually heard the original though? Beethoven decided to drop a full choir into the final movement of his ninth symphony, and despite being near death and almost entirely deaf, he composes this piece about-that's right-joy. The lyrics are entirely in German, and it became one of the most famous songs in history. Enjoy the masterpiece.

Title: Take Care
Comment:
Today everyone knows this as Drake’s song, but there's a rich musical history behind it, going back before rap was even invented.

In short, Rihanna's part is a cover of a 1959 song by Bobby Bland (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=V8stN0eGVAk)

The Bobby Bland song became a blues classic, covered by many, including a cover by poet/jazz legend Gil Scott Heron, which appeared on his final album in 2010 before he died in 2011 (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PXPN2dbgu5g)

In 2011, British artist Jamie XX did a remix of the Gil Scott Heron cover (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PaXslpx3MWY)

Finally, Drake sampled the Jamie XX beat and got Rhianna to cover the Gil Scott Heron cover of Bobby Bland. And that's how we got Take Care.

Some say that Gil Scott invented rap, but Bobby's song even predates his career. Like all great pop songs, Take Care has a tapestry of timeless influences. Drake's song has since been covered by many others; and so the meme carries on for yet another generation.

Title: On the Nature of Daylight
Artist(s): Max Richter, Louisa Fuller, Natalia Bonner, John Metcalfe, Philip Sheppard, Chris Worsey
Comment:
Max Richter originally composed this piece in 2003 as reflection on the Iraq War. The song has such a visceral and captivating emotional depth that it has since been used in dozens of films and TV shows including:

The Trip (2010)
Shutter Island (2010)
Jiro Dreams of Sushi (2011)
Disconnect (2012)
White Night (2012)
Luck – Episode Four (2012)
Sleepless in New York (2014)
The Face of an Angel (2014)
Sherpa (2015)
Me and Kaminski (2015)
Arrival (2016)
Castle Rock – from the episode “The Queen” (2018)
Togo (2019)
Eastenders – from 35th Anniversary episode (2020)
Amazing Stories (2020)
Through the Glass Darkly (2020)
The Handmaid’s Tale – from episode “Progress” (2021)
Kleo (2022)
The Last of Us – from the episode “Long Long Time” (2023)
